PhotonMomentumFormula

The Photon Momentum Formula

The momentum of a photon is directly proportional to its energy.

p = \frac{E}{c}

where:

p [var. scal. Momentum, M L T^{-1}, kg m s^{-1}] is the momentum of the photon
E [var. scal. Energy, M L^{2} T^{-2}, J] is the energy of the photon
c [const. scal. SpeedOfLight, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the speed of light in free space


variants:

In terms of frequency

p = \frac{hf}{c}



---

In terms of wavelength

p = \frac{h}{\lambda}



