derivation:

We start with the relativistic energy-momentum relation

$$E^{2} = p^{2}c^{2} + m_{0}^{2}c^{4}$$

Photons are massless, thus $m_{0} = 0$, and this relation becomes

$$E^{2} = p^{2}c^{2}$$

We can square-root both sides and then rearrange the equation to get

$$p = \frac{E}{c}$$


